CAPE TOWN - A man has been arrested in connection with a murder on a farm near Moorreesburg. A 65-year-old woman was stabbed to death and a man was wounded in Tuesday's attack. "The female victim was declared deceased on scene by medical  personnel and the male victim was taken to a medical facility for medical treatment. Cases of murder and attempted murder were opened for investigation. A 34-year-old male was arrested," said the police's Wesley Twigg.